OL,3,CWorkers walk out at ready meals
OL,4,Cfactory and warn supermarket shelves
OL,5,Cwill suffer
OL,7,FWorkers are angry over claims that the
OL,8,Fcompany plans to remove some paid
OL,9,Fbreaks, reduce other breaks and
OL,10,Feradicate any enhanced payments and
OL,11,Fdays off in lieu for working bank
OL,12,Fholidays.
OL,14,FWorkers who refuse the roughly 10% cut
OL,15,Fof their net income allegedly face
OL,16,Fthreats of "fire and rehire", implying
OL,17,Fjob loss without any severance or
OL,18,Fredundancy package.
