OL,3,CWorkers walk out at ready meals
OL,4,Cfactory and warn supermarket shelves
OL,5,Cwill suffer
OL,7,FUnite general secretary Sharon Graham
OL,8,Fsaid: "Oscar Mayer's behaviour towards
OL,9,Fthese already low paid workers is
OL,10,Fdespicable.
OL,12,F"There is no justification whatsoever
OL,13,Fto slash their pay or for the threats
OL,14,Fof fire and rehire ` an abhorrent
OL,15,Fpractice that should be banned
OL,16,Foutright. Our members are absolutely
OL,17,Fright to strike and they have Unite's
OL,18,Funflinching support."
OL,20,FThe strikes will take place from 12
OL,21,FSeptember to 10 October.
